result.execSummary:
On one or more charges, the deferred prosecution or sentencing agreement(s) on this case were fulfilled, and the charge(s) were dismissed.

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: The defendant shall not commit any criminal offenses; shall notify the Taylor County District Attorney's Office, as well as the Clerk of Court's office, of any change of address within ten days of said change.

timeConds.notes: The community service must be preapproved by the District Attorney.  Proof of said service must be provided to the District Attorney's office or submit some form of apology to a local sportsmen's group (possibly in person or at a meeting).  Proof of this apology must be provided to the Taylor County District Attorney's Office.

Pursuant to Deferred Entry of Judgment Agreement
to Modify Bond - Defendant may leave Wisconsin from 4/6/17 through 4/11/17

*Defendant shall not leave the State of Wisconsin without prior notice to and written approval of the Court. Defendant may leave the State of Wisconsin for employment purposes. Must report to the Taylor County Sheriff's Office for Booking Procedure.

Defendant Brandon S. Frischmann in court with attorney Karl J. Kelz.  Kristi S. Tlusty appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Plea agreement put into the record.  Plea of no contest to counts 1 and 2.  Plea colloquy.  Plea freely, voluntarily and intelligently; factual basis exists.  Court accepts defendant's plea and makes finding of guilt and defers entry of judgment.  Court dismisses and read in count 3.  Court dismisses Case No. 16FO94. Statement by Attorney Kelz.  Court modifies defendant's bond to travel outside the State of Wisconsin for employment purposes.  Court orders a deferred agreement for a period of one year with conditions of no new criminal charges; 20 hours of community service or some form of apology to local sportsmen's group upon successful completion the charges will be dismissed.  Court signs deferred agreement.  - rt
